1
00:01:18,375 --> 00:01:19,541
<i>Jonathan, hurry.</i>

2
00:01:19,625 --> 00:01:21,000
<i>Jonathan Kang.</i>

3
00:01:24,166 --> 00:01:26,750
<i>Jonathan, hurry up!</i>

4
00:01:30,416 --> 00:01:33,166
Hurry!

5
00:01:34,208 --> 00:01:35,500
Wait for me!

6
00:01:35,583 --> 00:01:36,916
I'm waiting.

7
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,416
Wait!

8
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:41,000
-Wait already!
-Don't run like that. It's dangerous!

9
00:01:43,583 --> 00:01:46,625
<i>Shane, do you still remember?</i>

10
00:01:47,458 --> 00:01:50,541
<i>Our relationship started from an order.</i>

11
00:01:56,833 --> 00:01:58,916
<i>Ever since I saw you,</i>

12
00:01:59,875 --> 00:02:01,916
<i>I knew you were different</i>
<i>from anyone else.</i>

13
00:02:02,875 --> 00:02:04,833
<i>But I was not brave.</i>

14
00:02:06,125 --> 00:02:08,083
<i>Not brave enough to stand by you.</i>

15
00:02:09,291 --> 00:02:10,916
<i>Who can tell me?</i>

16
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,875
<i>What planet do we live on?</i>

17
00:02:12,958 --> 00:02:15,208
<i>Earth.</i>

18
00:02:16,083 --> 00:02:18,625
That's right. Earth is a planet.

19
00:02:18,708 --> 00:02:21,250
Planets rotate around stars.

20
00:02:21,333 --> 00:02:24,750
So, our sun is a star.

21
00:02:29,041 --> 00:02:31,291
Ms. Lee, here's the new transfer student.

22
00:02:31,375 --> 00:02:32,458
Alright, thank you.

23
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:40,416
Everybody, this is the new
transfer student from Taipei.

24
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:42,166
Let's give her a warm welcome.

25
00:02:44,875 --> 00:02:46,458
You can sit over there for now.

26
00:02:47,708 --> 00:02:51,000
We'll ask her to introduce herself later.

27
00:02:51,083 --> 00:02:52,416
Okay, back to class.

28
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:55,416
Besides stars and planets,
there are also comets.

29
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:57,791
Every time a comet
visits our solar system,

30
00:02:57,875 --> 00:03:00,583
it brings unexpected surprises.

31
00:03:00,666 --> 00:03:02,041
When a comet visits,

32
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:04,916
it usually brings a beautiful spectacle.

33
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:07,708
Like what we call shooting stars.

34
00:03:07,791 --> 00:03:10,916
Jonathan, have you ever been to Taipei?

35
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,000
That's right. We make a wish.

36
00:03:13,083 --> 00:03:17,500
We wish for Mommy and Daddy's health

37
00:03:17,583 --> 00:03:19,458
or to become a good student.

38
00:03:19,541 --> 00:03:21,916
Everyone can make his own wish.

39
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,333
Remember that…

40
00:03:23,416 --> 00:03:24,958
Shane Yu, what are you doing?

41
00:03:25,041 --> 00:03:26,708
Both of you, stand up!

42
00:03:32,375 --> 00:03:36,166
<i>The rabbit hops and hops</i>

43
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:38,625
<i>Then it runs off</i>

44
00:03:38,708 --> 00:03:42,041
<i>And disappears</i>

45
00:03:42,125 --> 00:03:43,500
Stop!

46
00:03:43,583 --> 00:03:45,125
Stop looking outside.

47
00:03:45,708 --> 00:03:49,166
Shane Yu scared the new student so much
that her family decided to transfer again.

48
00:03:49,250 --> 00:03:51,083
If you don't behave,

49
00:03:51,166 --> 00:03:53,750
you will be punished too, like Shane.

50
00:03:53,833 --> 00:03:57,125
Yunxuan Lee and Chiawei Yan,
stop looking outside.

51
00:03:57,208 --> 00:03:58,750
Let's repeat the song.

52
00:03:58,833 --> 00:04:01,166
Three, two, one, sing!

53
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:04,708
<i>The rabbit hops and hops</i>

54
00:04:04,791 --> 00:04:06,708
<i>Then it runs off</i>

55
00:04:06,791 --> 00:04:10,166
<i>And disappears</i>

56
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:13,083
<i>The rabbit boasts</i>

57
00:04:13,166 --> 00:04:15,083
<i>I'm the fastest</i>

58
00:04:16,416 --> 00:04:18,791
Jonathan Kang, sing again.

59
00:04:32,291 --> 00:04:35,833
<i>He's very naughty</i>
<i>and gets into trouble all the time.</i>

60
00:04:35,916 --> 00:04:37,958
I sent him to see the doctor before.

61
00:04:38,041 --> 00:04:39,541
The doctor suggested that

62
00:04:39,625 --> 00:04:44,291
if he can pair up with another student,
it will help modify his behavior,

63
00:04:44,375 --> 00:04:45,291
and he won't feel like
making trouble all the time.

64
00:04:45,375 --> 00:04:46,375
Everybody, stand!

65
00:04:47,791 --> 00:04:48,750
Attention!

66
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:50,791
Salute!

67
00:04:50,875 --> 00:04:54,041
Good morning, Teacher.

68
00:04:54,125 --> 00:04:55,333
Sit down.

69
00:04:55,416 --> 00:04:58,916
Jonathan Kang,
Ms. Lee wants to see you in her office.

70
00:05:00,125 --> 00:05:03,208
Please do your best for him.
Thank you so much.

71
00:05:03,291 --> 00:05:05,000
-I see.
-Thank you. I'll be leaving now.

72
00:05:05,083 --> 00:05:06,083
You're welcome.

73
00:05:06,166 --> 00:05:07,000
Yes, Teacher?

74
00:05:07,083 --> 00:05:08,291
Come here.

75
00:05:13,541 --> 00:05:16,458
I want you to do something for me.

76
00:05:16,541 --> 00:05:19,250
Teacher knows that you are a good student,

77
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:22,125
and Shane… Well, I would like

78
00:05:22,208 --> 00:05:24,000
to ask you
to become his little guardian angel,

79
00:05:24,083 --> 00:05:25,750
to help him and become friends with him.

80
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:28,791
This way, I believe, very soon,

81
00:05:28,875 --> 00:05:32,750
Shane will become a good student like you.

82
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:36,750
Will you do this for me?

83
00:05:38,625 --> 00:05:43,541
"Every time I face a challenge

84
00:05:43,625 --> 00:05:45,958
and feel defeated,

85
00:05:46,041 --> 00:05:50,416
my friend will say to me…"

86
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:51,458
Good morning.

87
00:05:51,541 --> 00:05:55,916
"'Tell me. What is your problem?

88
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,416
Let me help you.'

89
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:04,208
Every time I hear this,

90
00:06:04,291 --> 00:06:07,416
my courage comes back to me.

91
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:13,000
I am no longer scared,
I am no longer defeated.

92
00:06:13,083 --> 00:06:18,291
No matter how great the difficulty,
I will not run away.

93
00:06:18,375 --> 00:06:23,208
His words are as strong as shoulders."

94
00:06:23,291 --> 00:06:25,125
May I join you guys?

95
00:06:27,250 --> 00:06:29,083
Draw the portrait of the student
sitting across from you…

96
00:06:29,166 --> 00:06:30,791
May I join your group?

97
00:06:30,875 --> 00:06:32,083
…using your crayons.

98
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:34,833
May I join in?

99
00:06:34,916 --> 00:06:36,625
Some students are doing very well.

100
00:06:38,291 --> 00:06:40,000
Shane, why aren't you in a group?

101
00:06:41,583 --> 00:06:43,541
Does anyone want Shane in their group?

102
00:06:44,916 --> 00:06:47,333
Anyone?

103
00:06:47,416 --> 00:06:49,416
Yes, Teacher.
I volunteer to team up with Shane.

104
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:51,958
Okay, Jonathan, you two make a team, then.

105
00:06:57,916 --> 00:07:00,791
Let's go to the garden to play.

106
00:07:00,875 --> 00:07:03,541
No way.

107
00:07:03,625 --> 00:07:06,166
Jonathan Kang, you are my best friend.

108
00:07:09,416 --> 00:07:11,958
Chiwen Huang, 78.

109
00:07:15,125 --> 00:07:16,708
Anyone with less than 80,
step forward right now.

110
00:07:17,958 --> 00:07:20,333
Jonathan Kang, 67.

111
00:07:25,333 --> 00:07:27,833
Shame on you, class leader.
You've dropped so much.

112
00:07:29,666 --> 00:07:32,166
Li Hanjue, 84.

113
00:07:39,791 --> 00:07:42,166
I am not here to punish you,

114
00:07:42,250 --> 00:07:44,583
but you've really done too poorly.

115
00:07:44,666 --> 00:07:48,208
How can you feel good about yourself
with these grades?

116
00:07:48,291 --> 00:07:49,750
How can you let me down?

117
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:52,041
I have guided you through these questions

118
00:07:52,125 --> 00:07:53,916
again and again in class.

119
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,500
Here are the same questions on this exam,

120
00:07:56,583 --> 00:07:59,416
and you can't even get a B.

121
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:02,250
Don't you know
how much effort I've spent on you?

122
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:05,208
And this is the result?

123
00:08:15,333 --> 00:08:16,500
You know, Jonathan?

124
00:08:17,375 --> 00:08:19,416
If you add my mark with yours,
we make a perfect 100.

125
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:23,375
<i>Since then,</i>

126
00:08:23,458 --> 00:08:24,708
<i>I never stop wondering</i>

127
00:08:25,541 --> 00:08:27,458
<i>if I was brave enough</i>

128
00:08:27,541 --> 00:08:29,750
<i>to say "no" to the teacher,</i>

129
00:08:30,541 --> 00:08:32,250
<i>what kind of me will I become?</i>

130
00:08:32,333 --> 00:08:33,875
<i>Will I gain more</i>

131
00:08:34,375 --> 00:08:35,958
<i>or lose more?</i>

132
00:08:47,541 --> 00:08:48,666
Jonathan Kang!

133
00:08:50,958 --> 00:08:52,791
Jonathan Kang!

134
00:08:52,875 --> 00:08:53,958
Wake up!

135
00:08:54,541 --> 00:08:55,875
Jonathan!

136
00:09:00,208 --> 00:09:01,541
Jonathan!

137
00:09:03,708 --> 00:09:05,041
I'm coming!

138
00:09:05,125 --> 00:09:06,333
Jonathan!

139
00:09:07,083 --> 00:09:09,583
Jonathan!

140
00:09:10,708 --> 00:09:13,041
Jonathan!

141
00:09:13,125 --> 00:09:14,291
Jonathan!

142
00:09:14,375 --> 00:09:15,875
Hush, my family is still asleep.

143
00:09:15,958 --> 00:09:16,791
Hurry up, or you'll be late for school.

144
00:09:16,875 --> 00:09:17,958
Alright!

145
00:10:08,875 --> 00:10:10,166
Oh, so you're here!

146
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:11,083
What?

147
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:12,625
Why are you looking so depressed?

148
00:10:12,708 --> 00:10:15,083
Nothing. I'm just hanging.

149
00:10:15,166 --> 00:10:16,000
You know?

150
00:10:16,083 --> 00:10:17,916
My game went so bad after you left.

151
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,416
Like it has anything to do with me.

152
00:10:20,125 --> 00:10:22,083
What are you doing?

153
00:10:22,166 --> 00:10:23,166
Break time is over.

154
00:10:23,250 --> 00:10:24,666
Come on!

155
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:25,666
-Let's go!
-What are you doing?

156
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:26,916
Let go!

157
00:10:28,875 --> 00:10:30,000
Go away!

158
00:10:38,875 --> 00:10:40,083
I don't want to tell you.

159
00:10:40,916 --> 00:10:42,541
I won't tell you where I'm heading.

160
00:10:43,291 --> 00:10:45,208
I'll save the money myself.

161
00:10:47,166 --> 00:10:48,666
I will go to Taiwan. Hang up the phone.

162
00:11:12,041 --> 00:11:15,416
Carrie, you can't just come
to Taiwan all of a sudden.

163
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:16,958
Your dad will be worried.

164
00:11:17,750 --> 00:11:20,416
Why weren't you worried
when you dumped me in Hong Kong?

165
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:21,625
What was that?

166
00:11:22,208 --> 00:11:25,000
Why weren't you worried
when you dumped me by myself in Hong Kong?

167
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:27,625
I did not dump you
by yourself in Hong Kong.

168
00:11:27,708 --> 00:11:29,916
You've got your dad and auntie there.

169
00:11:30,541 --> 00:11:32,875
Besides, you chose to go to
Hong Kong in the first place.

170
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:38,875
Alright, just eat slowly.

171
00:11:42,958 --> 00:11:44,791
Good morning.

172
00:11:45,375 --> 00:11:47,791
Good morning.

173
00:11:48,291 --> 00:11:49,458
Okay, everybody, you can rest.

174
00:11:50,625 --> 00:11:52,875
Before I start my speech today,

175
00:11:52,958 --> 00:11:55,541
I would like to ask a student
to come on stage.

176
00:11:56,041 --> 00:11:58,208
Senior class B, Miss Carrie Tu.

177
00:12:01,625 --> 00:12:03,291
Carrie Tu, come up to the stage.

178
00:12:10,666 --> 00:12:11,958
Carrie Tu.

179
00:12:12,041 --> 00:12:16,958
Do you know why you are different
from all the other students?

180
00:12:23,708 --> 00:12:27,708
Please take a good look at Miss Tu

181
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:30,916
and see why she is different from you all.

182
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:35,208
Fine. Since you do not know the answer,

183
00:12:35,291 --> 00:12:36,916
let me tell you

184
00:12:37,916 --> 00:12:41,583
by making her the same as the rest of you.

185
00:12:47,125 --> 00:12:48,166
Quiet!

186
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:54,791
In future, I hope that every student

187
00:12:54,875 --> 00:12:56,916
will follow the school regulations

188
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,708
on wardrobe and hair.

189
00:12:59,708 --> 00:13:01,250
Carrie Tu, return to class.

190
00:13:10,958 --> 00:13:12,250
Are you okay?

191
00:13:15,125 --> 00:13:16,333
It's not a big deal.

192
00:13:16,416 --> 00:13:18,125
The hair will grow back.

193
00:13:18,666 --> 00:13:19,750
Don't think too much about it.

194
00:13:21,333 --> 00:13:22,375
Yeah.

195
00:13:37,208 --> 00:13:38,375
Jonathan.

196
00:13:39,958 --> 00:13:41,583
Wanna skip school and go to Taipei?

197
00:13:44,791 --> 00:13:46,208
Where to?

198
00:13:46,291 --> 00:13:47,375
Wait.

199
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,791
-Do you have enough?
-Yeah, should be.

200
00:13:50,875 --> 00:13:52,125
Okay, should be enough.

201
00:13:52,208 --> 00:13:53,208
Alright.

202
00:13:53,708 --> 00:13:55,666
-Where to?
-Two tickets to Taipei.

203
00:14:06,291 --> 00:14:07,208
I wanted to ask you…

204
00:14:07,291 --> 00:14:08,416
Don't peep. Go away!

205
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:09,833
Sorry.

206
00:14:10,666 --> 00:14:12,208
-I just wanted to ask.
-What?

207
00:14:12,291 --> 00:14:13,791
What if we get caught?

208
00:14:13,875 --> 00:14:14,791
They won't.

209
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:16,916
Don't peak.

210
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,875
Cover me.

211
00:14:20,833 --> 00:14:21,791
Hush.

212
00:14:55,125 --> 00:14:56,541
Let me see.

213
00:14:57,666 --> 00:14:58,916
You look nice.

214
00:15:08,583 --> 00:15:09,500
Okay?

215
00:15:23,750 --> 00:15:26,666
Jonathan, how many girlfriends
have you had?

216
00:15:26,750 --> 00:15:28,500
Never, and you?

217
00:15:30,041 --> 00:15:31,166
So many.

218
00:15:31,250 --> 00:15:32,375
No way.

219
00:15:35,791 --> 00:15:36,625
Let's go!

220
00:16:14,916 --> 00:16:16,791
Let's stay in Taipei tonight?

221
00:16:33,791 --> 00:16:35,041
Wait for me.

222
00:16:35,125 --> 00:16:36,000
Hush.

223
00:17:45,791 --> 00:17:46,833
How do we begin?

224
00:17:50,375 --> 00:17:51,583
You first.

225
00:17:52,750 --> 00:17:54,083
Take off your clothes.

226
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:12,666
The following are some common traits
of the solubility of alkali.

227
00:20:12,750 --> 00:20:16,125
First, it has a bitter taste
and a splendid look.

228
00:20:16,208 --> 00:20:20,416
Second, it turns red litmus paper blue.

229
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:24,375
Third, with acid, it will compose salt.

230
00:20:24,458 --> 00:20:25,791
Scientists in the early days

231
00:20:25,875 --> 00:20:28,458
distinguished a substance
according to these common traits.

232
00:21:25,291 --> 00:21:30,041
<i>THEORY OF TRANSGENDER</i>

233
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:34,416
-My God, you're so slow.
-No, I'm not.

234
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,791
Hurry. Let's go.

235
00:21:40,416 --> 00:21:41,791
Hold on for me.

236
00:21:42,458 --> 00:21:44,458
-Jonathan, you know what?
-What?

237
00:21:44,541 --> 00:21:46,500
Which university are you
planning to go to?

238
00:21:46,583 --> 00:21:48,583
You're not getting into any university.
Why do you ask?

239
00:21:49,125 --> 00:21:50,875
But I made it to high school this far.

240
00:21:50,958 --> 00:21:52,291
You just got lucky.

241
00:21:52,375 --> 00:21:54,166
Maybe I'll be lucky again this time.

242
00:21:54,250 --> 00:21:55,583
It will take a miracle
for you to pass the exam.

243
00:21:56,083 --> 00:21:58,000
If I can help the school team
win the championship,

244
00:21:58,083 --> 00:21:59,416
I'll be recommended to a university
regardless of the exam.

245
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:01,125
Fine, then. I'll flunk the exam,

246
00:22:01,208 --> 00:22:02,083
and you can go to university
all by yourself.

247
00:22:02,166 --> 00:22:03,583
Why do you say things like that?

248
00:22:03,666 --> 00:22:04,625
Sit tight.

249
00:22:05,291 --> 00:22:06,333
What?

250
00:22:24,458 --> 00:22:26,333
Didn't we agree to go to
the same university together?

251
00:22:26,416 --> 00:22:27,375
We'll see.

252
00:22:27,458 --> 00:22:28,666
Why do you say that?

253
00:22:30,375 --> 00:22:31,333
Look.

254
00:22:32,875 --> 00:22:33,791
Hey!

255
00:22:34,458 --> 00:22:35,583
Hey!

256
00:22:37,083 --> 00:22:38,416
Hey!

257
00:22:43,666 --> 00:22:45,083
What now?

258
00:22:45,166 --> 00:22:46,458
Who's that?

259
00:22:46,541 --> 00:22:48,375
Nobody. None of your business.

260
00:22:48,458 --> 00:22:49,750
Says who?

261
00:22:51,500 --> 00:22:52,583
Don't go after her!

262
00:22:52,666 --> 00:22:54,125
Why not?

263
00:22:54,208 --> 00:22:56,000
Stop it, Shane.

264
00:22:56,083 --> 00:22:57,541
You don't know her anyway.

265
00:22:58,125 --> 00:22:59,166
Shane.

266
00:22:59,250 --> 00:23:00,250
Come on!

267
00:23:01,291 --> 00:23:03,041
Let's go. Stop goofing around.

268
00:23:03,125 --> 00:23:04,875
Come on. Go back now.

269
00:23:04,958 --> 00:23:06,416
Shane.

270
00:23:06,500 --> 00:23:08,291
Stop it, Shane!

271
00:23:11,958 --> 00:23:13,000
Stop it!

