I'm lying to him when I see him.

553
00:56:15,166 --> 00:56:16,541
Maybe not right now.

554
00:56:17,166 --> 00:56:18,625
Wait until he finishes his exams.

555
00:56:22,458 --> 00:56:23,458
Oh.

556
00:56:47,166 --> 00:56:48,583
Why did you call me?

557
00:56:48,666 --> 00:56:50,500
I'm so bored. Hang out with me.

558
00:56:50,583 --> 00:56:51,791
I have to go to the cram school.

559
00:56:54,708 --> 00:56:56,083
Let's go.

560
00:56:56,625 --> 00:56:58,083
I have an exam.

561
00:56:59,791 --> 00:57:00,916
Let's go.

562
00:57:08,750 --> 00:57:10,000
Go.

563
00:57:10,708 --> 00:57:12,083
I beg you!

564
00:57:37,708 --> 00:57:40,208
CARRIE CALLING

565
00:57:50,375 --> 00:57:53,208
Jonathan, are you home?

566
00:58:15,250 --> 00:58:16,583
Jonathan.

567
00:58:55,250 --> 00:58:58,041
CARRIE CALLING

568
00:59:07,958 --> 00:59:10,791
<i>Your call has been forwarded</i>
<i>to a voicemail box.</i>

569
00:59:29,750 --> 00:59:32,708
CHEER UP!

570
00:59:45,875 --> 00:59:47,416
Why is it pouring like this suddenly?

571
00:59:48,541 --> 00:59:49,791
Move over.

572
00:59:50,541 --> 00:59:51,958
Move over a little.

573
00:59:59,916 --> 01:00:03,375
Carrie just called
while we were riding the bike.

574
01:00:07,791 --> 01:00:09,166
You've been hanging out with her recently?

575
01:00:15,958 --> 01:00:17,500
So, you're like boyfriend-girlfriend?

576
01:00:27,833 --> 01:00:28,875
Look, I'm sorry.

577
01:00:29,708 --> 01:00:31,583
I know Carrie used to be your girlfriend,

578
01:00:32,416 --> 01:00:34,666
but then she started to come see me
play basketball games.

579
01:00:35,291 --> 01:00:36,708
I know you guys were together before.

580
01:00:36,791 --> 01:00:38,083
The school paper thing.

581
01:00:39,750 --> 01:00:41,541
I didn't go out with her in high school.

582
01:00:42,083 --> 01:00:43,666
She said

583
01:00:43,750 --> 01:00:45,291
she would only go out with me
if I make it to university.

584
01:00:45,375 --> 01:00:46,333
Shane.

585
01:00:50,958 --> 01:00:52,083
I need to ask you something,

586
01:00:52,166 --> 01:00:53,541
and I want you to give me
an honest answer.

587
01:00:56,000 --> 01:00:57,541
Carrie is my good friend.

588
01:01:00,125 --> 01:01:01,708
Do you really like her,

589
01:01:04,333 --> 01:01:05,875
or are you just fooling around with her?

590
01:01:14,291 --> 01:01:15,750
I really like her.

591
01:01:18,750 --> 01:01:23,166
I wanted to tell you before,
but I know you're preparing for exams.

592
01:01:23,250 --> 01:01:24,583
I was worried that it would affect you.

593
01:01:26,708 --> 01:01:30,791
If you give me another chance,
I would tell you right away.

594
01:01:36,375 --> 01:01:38,750
I'm going. Why don't you go see her?

595
01:01:38,833 --> 01:01:40,625
Jonathan, what is it?

596
01:01:40,708 --> 01:01:41,833
What are you?

597
01:01:48,541 --> 01:01:49,708
Jonathan!

598
01:04:10,750 --> 01:04:11,958
Hello?

599
01:04:12,541 --> 01:04:13,541
Shane.

600
01:04:16,791 --> 01:04:18,166
What?

601
01:04:18,250 --> 01:04:19,500
Slow down.

602
01:04:29,833 --> 01:04:31,666
How did he find out?

603
01:04:36,750 --> 01:04:37,708
Uh.

604
01:06:05,000 --> 01:06:06,708
<i>A new message.</i>

605
01:06:06,791 --> 01:06:07,958
<i>Hello, Jonathan?</i>

606
01:06:08,541 --> 01:06:09,708
<i>This is Shane.</i>

607
01:06:10,833 --> 01:06:11,708
<i>You turned off your phone.</i>

608
01:06:11,791 --> 01:06:13,500
<i>I couldn't reach you.</i>

609
01:06:15,125 --> 01:06:16,500
<i>Anyway,</i>

610
01:06:17,916 --> 01:06:19,333
<i>I just want to let you know</i>

611
01:06:20,500 --> 01:06:22,666
<i>I'm sorry. I really didn't mean it.</i>

612
01:06:23,875 --> 01:06:25,791
<i>You're really important to me.</i>

613
01:06:28,250 --> 01:06:31,916
<i>Anyway, please call me</i>
<i>when you get this message.</i>

614
01:06:52,166 --> 01:06:53,458
Jonathan.

615
01:06:59,041 --> 01:07:00,333
What?

616
01:07:00,416 --> 01:07:01,541
Sit down.

617
01:07:05,958 --> 01:07:08,500
You can tell someone to take your shift.

618
01:07:11,208 --> 01:07:13,583
Our faculty ball is tonight.
You wanna come?

619
01:07:27,000 --> 01:07:29,541
Shane, are you coming with us
or getting there yourself?

620
01:07:29,625 --> 01:07:30,916
I don't think I'll go after all.

621
01:07:31,000 --> 01:07:32,666
Why not? You said you would.

622
01:07:32,750 --> 01:07:33,583
Why not all of a sudden?

623
01:07:33,666 --> 01:07:34,708
Party's no fun if you're not there.

624
01:07:34,791 --> 01:07:36,791
Jonathan's busy tonight.

625
01:07:36,875 --> 01:07:38,250
I have to take him home.

626
01:07:38,333 --> 01:07:39,625
What? We're still going
even if we have to work tonight.

627
01:07:39,708 --> 01:07:41,500
Let's all go together.

628
01:07:42,875 --> 01:07:43,958
Yeah, you go.

629
01:07:44,041 --> 01:07:45,375
I'll go home by myself.

630
01:07:45,458 --> 01:07:46,708
See? He can take care of himself.

631
01:07:46,791 --> 01:07:47,875
You should come with us.

632
01:07:47,958 --> 01:07:50,250
-Come on.
-Please.

633
01:07:50,333 --> 01:07:52,333
Stop being so…

634
01:07:52,416 --> 01:07:54,416
Stop being so difficult. Just come!

635
01:07:54,958 --> 01:07:56,166
It's going to be fun.

636
01:07:56,250 --> 01:07:57,375
Fine. How about this, then?

637
01:07:57,458 --> 01:07:58,666
What?

638
01:07:59,458 --> 01:08:01,375
I'll go if Jonathan goes.

639
01:08:01,458 --> 01:08:02,750
Jonathan, come with us.

640
01:08:02,833 --> 01:08:03,750
Please, Jonathan, please come.

641
01:08:03,833 --> 01:08:05,041
Hey! Don't drag me into this.

642
01:08:05,125 --> 01:08:06,958
Would you stop wondering?

643
01:08:09,000 --> 01:08:10,625
Come. It's going to be fun.

644
01:08:10,708 --> 01:08:12,166
-Don't be a party pooper.
-It'll be fun!

645
01:08:12,250 --> 01:08:13,791
Please, I beg you.

646
01:08:14,375 --> 01:08:15,208
Please come.

647
01:08:15,291 --> 01:08:16,625
Don't let us down.

648
01:08:16,708 --> 01:08:18,666
Stop thinking. Just say yes.

649
01:08:18,750 --> 01:08:19,916
Please.

650
01:08:20,000 --> 01:08:21,333
Alright, I'll go.

651
01:08:30,291 --> 01:08:33,000
The turtle races against the hare
and the pig is the referee.

652
01:08:33,083 --> 01:08:33,916
Who wins?

653
01:08:34,000 --> 01:08:35,000
The turtle.

654
01:08:35,083 --> 01:08:35,958
You're a pig yourself.

655
01:08:36,041 --> 01:08:38,666
No, you are pig!

656
01:08:39,916 --> 01:08:41,333
My friend's here.

657
01:08:41,416 --> 01:08:42,291
I'll be right back.

658
01:08:42,375 --> 01:08:44,000
Okay, later.

659
01:08:50,375 --> 01:08:51,750
Why do you look so bored?

660
01:08:51,833 --> 01:08:54,416
Nothing. You go have fun.

661
01:08:55,000 --> 01:08:56,500
We'll have fun together.

662
01:08:56,583 --> 01:08:57,541
Carrie's joining us later.

663
01:08:57,625 --> 01:08:58,875
She can be your company.

664
01:09:00,541 --> 01:09:02,833
How about if we play a game?

665
01:09:07,208 --> 01:09:08,416
What game?

666
01:09:09,250 --> 01:09:10,958
Those girls over there
were just teaching me

667
01:09:11,041 --> 01:09:12,416
a "choose one out of two" game.

668
01:09:12,500 --> 01:09:13,958
You have to choose one out of the two

669
01:09:14,041 --> 01:09:15,125
or you have to tell the truth.

670
01:09:16,375 --> 01:09:17,958
I don't want to play.

671
01:09:18,041 --> 01:09:19,125
Come on.

672
01:09:19,208 --> 01:09:20,208
I don't want to play.

673
01:09:21,250 --> 01:09:22,500
I don't care. I'll start first anyway.

674
01:09:23,291 --> 01:09:24,625
Your dad or your mom?

675
01:09:25,916 --> 01:09:26,958
Both.

676
01:09:28,083 --> 01:09:29,791
You have to choose one.

677
01:09:30,833 --> 01:09:32,291
My mom.

678
01:09:32,375 --> 01:09:33,333
Hair or eyebrows?

679
01:09:34,416 --> 01:09:35,416
Whose?

680
01:09:36,208 --> 01:09:37,458
Yours, of course.

681
01:09:38,916 --> 01:09:40,125
Hair.

682
01:09:41,208 --> 01:09:42,666
Tits or ass?

683
01:09:44,666 --> 01:09:46,250
Ass.

684
01:09:46,333 --> 01:09:47,708
Brains or body?

685
01:09:51,083 --> 01:09:52,416
Brains.

686
01:09:52,500 --> 01:09:55,333
Liar! You think I don't know
the real answer to that?

687
01:09:56,166 --> 01:09:57,500
Now, it's your turn to ask me.

688
01:09:58,250 --> 01:10:00,375
-Nah.
-Just ask.

689
01:10:00,458 --> 01:10:01,875
I don't know what to ask.

690
01:10:04,625 --> 01:10:06,000
Alright.

691
01:10:07,250 --> 01:10:09,416
-Black or white?
-What?

692
01:10:09,500 --> 01:10:12,791
-Black or white?
-Black.

693
01:10:12,875 --> 01:10:15,166
-Fruit or cake?
-Fruit.

694
01:10:15,916 --> 01:10:18,125
-Cat or dog?
-Dog.

695
01:10:21,125 --> 01:10:22,166
Go on!

696
01:10:22,250 --> 01:10:24,416
Okay, let me think.

697
01:10:24,500 --> 01:10:26,250
Bring it on.

698
01:10:27,000 --> 01:10:29,916
Me or Carrie?

699
01:10:32,125 --> 01:10:33,416
What?

700
01:10:41,166 --> 01:10:42,666
I'm going to the washroom.

701
01:10:49,875 --> 01:10:50,875
Where's Jonathan?

702
01:10:52,041 --> 01:10:53,125
Jonathan.

703
01:11:39,250 --> 01:11:40,208
Shane, Carrie.

704
01:11:40,750 --> 01:11:43,000
I'm busy tomorrow. I have to go.

705
01:11:45,666 --> 01:11:47,250
What's up with you?

706
01:11:47,333 --> 01:11:51,666
Nothing. You guys have fun.
I'm busy tomorrow. I have to go.

707
01:11:51,750 --> 01:11:53,083
What do you want me to do?

708
01:11:54,166 --> 01:11:56,083
I really have to study for tomorrow!

709
01:11:56,166 --> 01:11:59,583
And so many other things. I'm really busy.
There's so much to do. I have to go.

710
01:11:59,666 --> 01:12:01,916
If you go, Carrie's going to think
you're upset.

711
01:12:02,000 --> 01:12:02,958
It's been so long
since the three of us can get together

712
01:12:03,041 --> 01:12:05,208
and have some fun.
Why do you have to act this way?

713
01:12:08,625 --> 01:12:11,291
Shane, I mean it.

714
01:12:11,375 --> 01:12:13,750
We don't have to be
with each other all the time.

715
01:12:13,833 --> 01:12:16,500
You've got your life, I've got mine.

716
01:12:16,583 --> 01:12:17,708
It's all the same for me.

717
01:12:17,791 --> 01:12:19,541
It's not a problem at all.

718
01:12:19,625 --> 01:12:21,583
Besides, aren't we best friends?

719
01:12:21,666 --> 01:12:24,708
What can't you tell me?
Are you hiding something from me?

720
01:12:34,583 --> 01:12:35,625
Best friends?

721
01:12:38,583 --> 01:12:41,541
Fine. Let me tell you this.

722
01:12:42,833 --> 01:12:43,958
I…

723
01:12:44,458 --> 01:12:46,750
I never volunteered to be your friend.

724
01:12:48,666 --> 01:12:51,833
In childhood, the teacher forced me to.

725
01:12:52,750 --> 01:12:54,416
I never wanted to be friends!

726
01:14:13,333 --> 01:14:14,291
Hello?

727
01:14:18,875 --> 01:14:20,041
Yes.

728
01:14:20,791 --> 01:14:22,333
That's right. I know him.

729
01:14:29,166 --> 01:14:30,291
Keys.

730
01:15:00,541 --> 01:15:01,916
Let's go.

731
01:17:21,916 --> 01:17:23,083
What?

732
01:17:28,541 --> 01:17:29,541
What?

733
01:17:31,583 --> 01:17:32,583
What are you doing?

734
01:17:38,958 --> 01:17:40,208
What?

735
01:17:41,875 --> 01:17:43,875
Are you drunk or something?

736
01:17:49,291 --> 01:17:50,416
What the hell are you doing?

737
01:17:51,833 --> 01:17:53,333
Are you losing your head?

738
01:17:57,541 --> 01:18:00,291
Shane, are you messing with me?

739
01:19:37,750 --> 01:19:38,833
Hello?

740
01:19:39,458 --> 01:19:40,666
<i>Is this Carrie?</i>

741
01:19:42,166 --> 01:19:43,416
<i>This is Jonathan.</i>

742
01:19:44,000 --> 01:19:45,541
<i>Shane is at my place now.</i>

743
01:19:46,166 --> 01:19:47,333
<i>Do you want to come here?</i>

744
01:19:49,041 --> 01:19:51,041
<i>Can you promise me one thing?</i>

745
01:19:52,916 --> 01:19:56,583
<i>No matter what happens,</i>
<i>you guys have to always stay together.</i>

746
01:20:00,041 --> 01:20:01,291
You're awake.

747
01:20:06,916 --> 01:20:08,333
Where's Jonathan?

748
01:20:08,416 --> 01:20:09,958
I don't know.

749
01:20:10,041 --> 01:20:13,083
He called me this morning
and told me you're here.

750
01:20:13,708 --> 01:20:15,291
So I came.

751
01:20:15,375 --> 01:20:18,000
And he was gone already.

752
01:20:31,791 --> 01:20:33,541
You can't see the ocean in Taipei.

753
01:20:38,500 --> 01:20:40,958
-You know?
-What?

754
01:20:41,041 --> 01:20:43,541
When I was a child,
I was the kind everybody hated.

755
01:20:44,291 --> 01:20:45,583
You still are.

756
01:20:50,791 --> 01:20:52,125
I'm serious.

757
01:20:52,958 --> 01:20:54,625
I was a real troublemaker.

758
01:20:55,791 --> 01:20:58,625
One time, I don't know why,
but I suddenly took a pair of scissors

759
01:20:58,708 --> 01:21:01,166
and cut the hair of the girl
sitting in front of me.

760
01:21:02,916 --> 01:21:04,625
The teacher was so furious.

761
01:21:05,125 --> 01:21:06,666
You know what she did to me?

762
01:21:12,208 --> 01:21:14,458
She sent me and my desk
and chair to the middle of the field

763
01:21:16,208 --> 01:21:17,916
and forbid me from having class
with the others.

764
01:21:19,666 --> 01:21:22,708
Everybody was scared to be my friend.

765
01:21:31,458 --> 01:21:33,708
Even now,
I'm still afraid of that feeling.

766
01:21:40,541 --> 01:21:42,375
Then Jonathan came along.

767
01:21:43,708 --> 01:21:45,666
No matter what trouble I got myself into,

768
01:21:46,291 --> 01:21:47,958
he would still stick with me.

769
01:21:52,083 --> 01:21:54,208
He was my only friend.

770
01:22:11,541 --> 01:22:13,166
Then you came along.

771
01:22:19,875 --> 01:22:22,166
I cannot lose any one of you.

772
01:22:33,000 --> 01:22:34,583
We've really grown up.

773
01:22:39,166 --> 01:22:40,500
When you grow up,

774
01:22:42,166 --> 01:22:43,625
everything changes.

775
01:25:40,583 --> 01:25:42,541
<i>Is this Carrie? It's Shane.</i>

776
01:25:47,958 --> 01:25:49,416
Where did you get the car?

777
01:25:50,041 --> 01:25:51,833
Some senior on the team.

778
01:25:51,916 --> 01:25:52,958
Drive carefully, then.

779
01:25:53,041 --> 01:25:54,625
Don't crash the car.

780
01:25:55,666 --> 01:25:57,375
Taking trains is more convenient.

781
01:25:57,458 --> 01:25:59,083
Why must you insist on driving?

782
01:26:04,125 --> 01:26:06,041
Since we're traveling south,

783
01:26:06,125 --> 01:26:08,333
it's better to drive than queue
for train tickets.

784
01:26:09,750 --> 01:26:11,875
You can book tickets online now.

785
01:26:11,958 --> 01:26:13,375
There's no need to queue.

786
01:26:34,791 --> 01:26:36,750
Shane, where are we?

787
01:26:36,833 --> 01:26:38,375
Why did you bring us here?

788
01:26:38,875 --> 01:26:40,500
Shane Yu.

789
01:26:41,791 --> 01:26:42,916
Shane!

790
01:26:51,125 --> 01:26:52,333
Jonathan.

791
01:26:52,416 --> 01:26:53,375
Yeah?

792
01:26:53,458 --> 01:26:54,833
Wanna take a walk?

793
01:26:58,791 --> 01:27:00,166
I'm going, then.

794
01:27:11,416 --> 01:27:12,666
You really don't want to go?

795
01:27:12,750 --> 01:27:15,333
You go. I'll wait for you guys in the car.

796
01:27:35,166 --> 01:27:38,416
You know what? I've been thinking.

797
01:27:40,500 --> 01:27:43,416
Maybe I'm too used to
having Jonathan by my side.

798
01:27:44,750 --> 01:27:46,875
Too used to having both of you
take care of me.

799
01:27:51,750 --> 01:27:52,708
Carrie.

800
01:27:55,041 --> 01:27:57,000
Will we lose each other in the future?

801
01:28:04,458 --> 01:28:06,833
Did I mess everything up?

802
01:28:07,708 --> 01:28:09,750
Am I the one who messes everything up?

803
01:28:23,625 --> 01:28:24,625
Hey!

804
01:28:27,916 --> 01:28:29,125
Shane.

805
01:28:29,791 --> 01:28:31,833
I think we should not see
each other anymore.

806
01:28:35,333 --> 01:28:36,791
What?

807
01:28:36,875 --> 01:28:40,833
I mean, it's not your fault.

808
01:28:42,166 --> 01:28:43,666
It's my own problem.

809
01:28:45,541 --> 01:28:47,333
Let's not see each other anymore.

810
01:28:50,000 --> 01:28:51,166
I mean it.

811
01:28:51,916 --> 01:28:53,750
There are so many things you don't know.

812
01:28:58,375 --> 01:28:59,541
Shane.

813
01:29:01,916 --> 01:29:03,375
-What are you doing?
-Stop fighting!

814
01:29:03,458 --> 01:29:05,166
No, stop it!

815
01:29:05,250 --> 01:29:06,125
What are you doing?

816
01:29:06,208 --> 01:29:08,083
-Stop it!
-What is it?

817
01:29:16,666 --> 01:29:18,041
Stop fighting!

818
01:29:21,583 --> 01:29:23,625
Just say it, okay?

819
01:29:28,458 --> 01:29:29,750
I'll wait in the car.

820
01:29:47,875 --> 01:29:51,041
Sorry.

821
01:29:51,625 --> 01:29:53,291
I shouldn't say it like that.

822
01:29:56,708 --> 01:29:59,541
I just want to know
if you really meant what you said.

823
01:30:00,291 --> 01:30:01,583
I don't know.

824
01:30:02,125 --> 01:30:03,916
What do you mean you don't know?

825
01:30:04,000 --> 01:30:04,958
I…

826
01:30:10,791 --> 01:30:12,208
Aren't we best friends?

827
01:30:13,166 --> 01:30:15,041
What can't you tell me?

828
01:30:20,333 --> 01:30:21,416
Shane.

829
01:30:22,166 --> 01:30:24,375
You said best friends
can tell each other anything.

830
01:30:25,541 --> 01:30:26,708
Fine.

831
01:30:28,166 --> 01:30:29,708
Then I really want to know

832
01:30:31,041 --> 01:30:34,875
if you'll still be my friend
after you hear my secret.

833
01:30:40,416 --> 01:30:41,500
Shane.

834
01:30:42,833 --> 01:30:44,750
You're not just a friend to me.

835
01:30:46,000 --> 01:30:47,500
I really love you.

836
01:31:03,958 --> 01:31:04,916
Wait!

837
01:31:06,333 --> 01:31:08,458
I have a secret for you, too.

838
01:31:15,291 --> 01:31:17,000
Mrs. Yu,
your son's attention deficit disorder

839
01:31:17,083 --> 01:31:20,333
can be improved through group interaction.

840
01:31:20,416 --> 01:31:22,875
Help him find some kids

841
01:31:22,958 --> 01:31:24,166
to play with him.

842
01:31:24,250 --> 01:31:28,375
That way, I believe his condition
will slowly improve.

843
01:31:30,625 --> 01:31:33,583
I always knew you were forced
by the teacher.

844
01:31:40,000 --> 01:31:42,750
I always knew you didn't volunteer
to be my friend.

845
01:31:50,375 --> 01:31:53,000
At first, I wanted to hurt you
and get you into trouble, too.

846
01:31:55,208 --> 01:31:57,375
But then I realized that I couldn't do it.

847
01:32:01,416 --> 01:32:03,166
I'm really too lonely.

848
01:32:11,000 --> 01:32:12,333
Jonathan Kang.

849
01:32:16,291 --> 01:32:18,166
You really are my best friend.
